<paragraph blockId="24.[264,1322,1713,1899]" lastBlockId="25.[264,1323,284,350]" lastPageId="25" lastPageNumber="26" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">
The subgenus 
<taxonomicName box="[435,613,1713,1738]" class="Ophiuroidea" family="Ophiopyrgidae" genus="Ophiuroglypha" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ophiurida" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[435,613,1713,1738]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">Ophiuroglypha</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is usually recognised as having 
<number box="[995,1009,1713,1739]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" value="3.0">3</number>
small armspines, the middle one becoming an upturned hooklet on distal arm segments (
<bibRefCitation author="Hertz" box="[1012,1157,1753,1779]" pageId="24" pageNumber="33" refString="Hertz, M. (1927) Die Ophiuroiden der Deutschen Tiefsee- Expedition. Wissenschaftliche Ergebnisse der Deutchen Tiefsee-Expedition auf den Damfer Valdivia 1898 - 1899, 22 (3), 59 - 122" type="journal article" year="1927">
Hertz, 
<number box="[1094,1157,1753,1779]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" value="1927.0">1927</number>
</bibRefCitation>
). However 
<taxonomicName class="Ophiuroidea" family="Ophiopyrgidae" genus="Ophiuroglypha" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ophiurida" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="species" species="irrorata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">O. irrorata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
includes subspecies (
<taxonomicName box="[618,718,1793,1818]" class="Ophiuroidea" family="Ophiopyrgidae" genus="Ophiuroglypha" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ophiurida" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="species" species="loveni">
<emphasis box="[618,718,1793,1818]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">O.loveni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName box="[732,912,1793,1818]" class="Ophiuroidea" family="Ophiopyrgidae" genus="Ophiuroglypha" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ophiurida" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="species" species="polyacantha">
<emphasis box="[732,912,1793,1818]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">O. polyacantha</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) with up to 
<number box="[1053,1068,1793,1819]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" value="9.0">9</number>
armspines, which are hooked or not. The 
<taxonomicName box="[505,636,1833,1858]" class="Ophiuroidea" family="Ophiopyrgidae" genus="Ophiuroglypha" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ophiurida" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="species" species="irrorata">
<emphasis box="[505,636,1833,1858]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">O. irrorata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group (
<bibRefCitation author="Paterson" box="[732,912,1833,1859]" pageId="24" pageNumber="34" refString="Paterson, G. L. J. (1985) The deep-sea Ophiuroidea of the North Atlantic Ocean. Bulletin of the British Museum (Natural History) Zoology, 49 (1), 1 - 162." type="journal article" year="1985">
Paterson, 
<number box="[852,912,1833,1859]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" value="1985.0">1985</number>
</bibRefCitation>
) also has an enlarged and distinct distal tentacle­scale or supplementary ventral armplate. In 
<taxonomicName box="[951,1068,1873,1898]" class="Ophiuroidea" family="Ophiopyrgidae" genus="Ophiuroglypha" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ophiurida" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="species" species="rugosa">
<emphasis box="[951,1068,1873,1898]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">O. rugosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
this is small and usually hidden by the larger scales on the proximal pore margin. The discrepancies between species assigned to 
<taxonomicName box="[494,672,324,349]" class="Ophiuroidea" family="Ophiopyrgidae" genus="Ophiuroglypha" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ophiurida" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[494,672,324,349]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Ophiuroglypha</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
indicates that a revision of the subgenus is desirable.
</paragraph>
